main event: An unidentified flying object was observed over Yardley, Pennsylvania and Plattsburgh AFB, New York on January 25, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as resembling a shooting star, The observation lasted between 30 seconds to 3 minutes, Multiple witnesses included both civilians and military personnel, The object was reported as moving southbound with a bright light, There was no physical evidence found related to the object.
sighted object: one unidentified flying object resembling a shooting star
witness description: Two civilians and three military personnel, including pilots and air traffic controllers
